==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trussing
<hw>Truss"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch. &
Engin.)</fld> <def>The timbers, etc., which form a truss, taken
collectively.</def> <rj><au>Weale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch. & Engin.)</fld> <def>The art of stiffening or
bracing a set of timbers, or the like, by putting in struts, ties, etc.,
till it has something of the character of a truss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of a hawk, or other bird of prey, in seizing
its quarry, and soaring with it into air.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trust</ent>⟦br⟧
